SIMPLE: mourn
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mourn
<hw>Mourn</hw> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧rn)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Mourned</conjf> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧rnd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr.
& vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Mourning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>murnan</ets>; akin to OS. <ets>mornian</ets>, OHG.
<ets>mornen</ets>, Goth. <ets>ma⟦uacute⟧rnan</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To express or to feel grief or sorrow; to grieve; to be sorrowful;
to lament; to be in a state of grief or sadness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Abraham came to <qex>mourn</qex> for Sarah, and to weep for
her.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xxiii. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To wear the customary garb of a mourner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We <qex>mourn</qex> in black; why <qex>mourn</qex> we not in
blood?</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Grieve for an hour, perhaps, then <qex>mourn</qex> a year.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mourn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mourn
<hw>Mourn</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To grieve for; to
lament; to deplore; to bemoan; to bewail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As if he <qex>mourned</qex> his rival's ill success.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And looking over the hills, I <qex>mourn</qex>⟦br⟧
The darling who shall not return.</q> <rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To utter in a mournful manner or voice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The lovelorn nightingale⟦br⟧
Nightly to thee her sad song <qex>mourneth</qex> well.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Deplore</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mourne</ent>⟦br⟧
